column1: Fail if we cannot make output dirs",2023-01-23T14:34:15Z,J35P312
78f89961fa8dac4d5e090b347abe93c050c6eedc,Jessime Kirk,jessime.kirk@gmail.com,"Fail if we cannot make output dirs
Failing to create either of these two dirs should result in an immediate exit, as downstream code assumes that they've been created and will fail ungracefully, with a red-herring error.

Further, there are many reasons why `mkdir` can fail, not just because the ""Folder already exists"". For example, permissions issues can cause a failure, in which case the print statement is misleading.",2023-01-17T18:28:02Z,Jessime
